### Code: (üëà Click dropdown)![][image1]

/\*\*  
 \* n8n Code node: Build ASS subtitles with per-word highlight groups  
 \* Works with input shaped like:  
 \*   { data: \[ { words:\[{word,start,end},...\], segments:\[...\], ... } \] }  
 \* or directly { words:\[...\], segments:\[...\] }  
 \*/

//////////////////// CONFIG ////////////////////  
const CONFIG \= {  
  wordsToShow: 3,

  // Styling (ASS uses BGR hex in \&H...; white \= FFFFFF)  
  fontName: 'Arial',  
  fontSize: 60,  
  fontColor: 'FFFFFF',      // primary  
  outlineColor: '000000',   // outline  
  backgroundColor: '000000',

  // Highlight  
  highlightFontSize: 70,  
  highlightColor: '00FFFF', // cyan

  // Text options  
  bold: 10,  
  italic: 0,  
  underline: 0,  
  strikeout: 0,  
  scaleX: 100,  
  scaleY: 100,  
  spacing: 0,  
  angle: 0,

  // Border/shadow  
  borderStyle: 1,  // 1 \= outline \+ drop shadow  
  outline: 5,  
  shadow: 1,

  // Positioning  
  alignment: 2,    // 2 \= bottom-center (ASS 1..9 grid)  
  marginL: 10,  
  marginR: 10,  
  marginV: 600,

  // Video resolution (fallbacks used if not provided upstream)  
  videoWidth: null,   // set below from input or default  
  videoHeight: null,  // set below from input or default

  // Merge small gaps within the same word group (ms)  
  maxGapTimeMs: 1000,

  // Minimum on-screen duration for any word (sec)  
  minWordDurSec: 0.12,  
    
  // Tiny gap between groups to prevent overlap (sec)  
  crossGroupPadSec: 0.02,  
    
  // Output filename  
  outputFileName: 'sentence\_aware\_subtitles.ass',  
};

//////////////////// HELPERS ////////////////////  
function firstDefined(...vals) {  
  for (const v of vals) if (v \!== undefined && v \!== null) return v;  
  return undefined;  
}

function formatTime(sec) {  
  const s \= Math.max(0, Number(sec) || 0);  
  const h \= Math.floor(s / 3600);  
  const m \= Math.floor((s % 3600\) / 60);  
  const ss \= Math.floor(s % 60);  
  const cs \= Math.floor((s \- Math.floor(s)) \* 100);  
  return \`${h}:${m.toString().padStart(2,'0')}:${ss.toString().padStart(2,'0')}.${cs.toString().padStart(2,'0')}\`;  
}

function escASS(text) {  
  // Escape curly braces which have meaning in ASS  
  return String(text || '').replace(/\[{}\]/g, m \=\> (m \=== '{' ? '\\\\{' : '\\\\}'));  
}

function createSubtitleText(group, highlightIndex) {  
  let line \= '';  
  for (let i \= 0; i \< group.length; i++) {  
    if (i \> 0\) line \+= ' ';  
    const token \= escASS(group\[i\].word).trim();  
    if (i \=== highlightIndex) {  
      line \+= \`{\\\\fs${CONFIG.highlightFontSize}\\\\c\&H${CONFIG.highlightColor}&}${token}{\\\\r}\`;  
    } else {  
      line \+= token;  
    }  
  }  
  return line;  
}

function createGroups(words, maxPerGroup) {  
  const groups \= \[\];  
  let current \= \[\];  
  for (let i \= 0; i \< words.length; i++) {  
    const w \= words\[i\];  
    current.push(w);  
    const txt \= String(w.word || '').trim();  
    const endOfSentence \= /\[.\!?\]$/.test(txt);  
    const atLimit \= current.length \>= maxPerGroup;  
    const last \= i \=== words.length \- 1;  
    if (atLimit || endOfSentence || last) {  
      if (current.length) groups.push(current.slice());  
      current \= \[\];  
    }  
  }  
  if (current.length) groups.push(current);  
  return groups;  
}

//////////////////// INPUT NORMALIZATION ////////////////////  
// Take the first input item‚Äôs JSON  
const item \= $input.first().json;

// Detect the Whisper payload object (either at root or inside data\[0\])  
let response \= item;  
if (item && Array.isArray(item.data) && item.data\[0\]) {  
  response \= item.data\[0\];  
}

// Collect words (prefer detailed per-word timings)  
let words \= \[\];  
if (Array.isArray(response.words) && response.words.length) {  
  words \= response.words.map(w \=\> ({  
    word: String(w.word ?? ''),  
    start: Number(w.start ?? 0),  
    end: Number(w.end ?? 0),  
  }));  
} else if (Array.isArray(response.segments) && response.segments.length) {  
  // If segments have words, flatten; else fall back to one-line per segment  
  for (const seg of response.segments) {  
    if (Array.isArray(seg.words) && seg.words.length) {  
      for (const w of seg.words) {  
        words.push({  
          word: String(w.word ?? ''),  
          start: Number(w.start ?? seg.start ?? 0),  
          end: Number(w.end ?? seg.end ?? 0),  
        });  
      }  
    } else {  
      // Fallback: treat whole segment as one ‚Äúword‚Äù  
      words.push({  
        word: String(seg.text ?? '').trim(),  
        start: Number(seg.start ?? 0),  
        end: Number(seg.end ?? (Number(seg.start ?? 0\) \+ 0.6)),  
      });  
      // If we‚Äôre here, make the groups wide so we don‚Äôt do per-word highlight weirdness  
      CONFIG.wordsToShow \= Math.max(CONFIG.wordsToShow, 999);  
    }  
  }  
}

// Guard: if still no words, throw a clear error  
if (\!words.length) {  
  throw new Error('No words or segments found in input. Expected response.words\[\] or response.segments\[\].');  
}

// Sort by time  
words.sort((a, b) \=\> (a.start \- b.start));

// Ensure minimal durations and numeric types  
for (const w of words) {  
  w.start \= Number(w.start || 0);  
  let end \= Number(w.end || 0);  
  if (\!(end \> w.start)) end \= w.start \+ CONFIG.minWordDurSec;  
  w.end \= end;  
}

// Video resolution (take from input if present; else sensible defaults)  
CONFIG.videoWidth \= firstDefined(item.width, item.videoWidth, response.width, 1080);  
CONFIG.videoHeight \= firstDefined(item.height, item.videoHeight, response.height, 1920);

//////////////////// ASS HEADER ////////////////////  
let ass \= \`\[Script Info\]  
Title: Sentence-Aware Fixed Position Subtitles  
ScriptType: v4.00+  
PlayResX: ${CONFIG.videoWidth}  
PlayResY: ${CONFIG.videoHeight}

\[V4+ Styles\]  
Format: Name, Fontname, Fontsize, PrimaryColour, SecondaryColour, OutlineColour, BackColour, Bold, Italic, Underline, StrikeOut, ScaleX, ScaleY, Spacing, Angle, BorderStyle, Outline, Shadow, Alignment, MarginL, MarginR, MarginV, Encoding  
Style: Default,${CONFIG.fontName},${CONFIG.fontSize},\&H${CONFIG.fontColor},\&H${CONFIG.outlineColor},\&H${CONFIG.outlineColor},\&H${CONFIG.backgroundColor},${CONFIG.bold},${CONFIG.italic},${CONFIG.underline},${CONFIG.strikeout},${CONFIG.scaleX},${CONFIG.scaleY},${CONFIG.spacing},${CONFIG.angle},${CONFIG.borderStyle},${CONFIG.outline},${CONFIG.shadow},${CONFIG.alignment},${CONFIG.marginL},${CONFIG.marginR},${CONFIG.marginV},1

\[Events\]  
Format: Layer, Start, End, Style, Name, MarginL, MarginR, MarginV, Effect, Text  
\`;

//////////////////// BUILD LINES ////////////////////  
// Group all words by sentence-ish boundary and size  
const groups \= createGroups(words, CONFIG.wordsToShow);

// Make one line per word with highlight inside its group  
const lines \= \[\];  
for (const g of groups) {  
  for (let i \= 0; i \< g.length; i++) {  
    const w \= g\[i\];  
    const start \= Number(w.start);  
    const end \= Number(w.end);  
    lines.push({  
      group: g,       // reference to the group  
      hi: i,          // which word is highlighted  
      start,  
      end,  
      fStart: formatTime(start),  
      fEnd: formatTime(end),  
      text: createSubtitleText(g, i),  
    });  
  }  
}

// Extend small gaps within the same group so the caption stays visible  
for (let i \= 0; i \< lines.length \- 1; i++) {  
  const a \= lines\[i\];  
  const b \= lines\[i \+ 1\];  
  if (a.group \=== b.group) {  
    const gap \= b.start \- a.end;  
    if (gap \> 0 && gap \<= CONFIG.maxGapTimeMs / 1000\) {  
      a.end \= b.start;  
      a.fEnd \= formatTime(a.end);  
    }  
  }  
}

// Emit ASS dialogue lines  
for (const L of lines) {  
  ass \+= \`Dialogue: 0,${L.fStart},${L.fEnd},Default,,0,0,0,,${L.text}\\n\`;  
}

//////////////////// RETURN BINARY ////////////////////  
return \[{  
  json: { generated: true, width: CONFIG.videoWidth, height: CONFIG.videoHeight, words: words.length, lines: lines.length },  
  binary: {  
    data: {  
      data: Buffer.from(ass, 'utf8').toString('base64'),  
      mimeType: 'text/ass',  
      fileName: CONFIG.outputFileName,  
    },  
  },  
}\];

### Execute Command: (üëà Click dropdown)![][image2]

\#\!/bin/bash  
set \-euo pipefail

\# Inputs from previous nodes  
RID="{{ $('Caption').item.json.query.record\_id }}"  
IN="{{ $('Write2').item.json.fileName }}"        \# /videos/\<id\>\_in.mp4 from Write Binary  
ASS="{{ $json.fileName }}"                        \# /videos/\<id\>.ass from Create ASS  
OUT="/videos/${RID}\_with\_captions.mp4"

\# If you installed DejaVu system-wide, libass will find it by family name.  
\# No need for fontsdir if the font is in /usr/share/fonts.  
FONT\_FAMILY="DejaVu Sans"  
\# Optional: force bold on top of your ASS style  
FORCE\_STYLE="FontName=${FONT\_FAMILY},Bold=1"

\# Burn subtitles  
ffmpeg \-hide\_banner \-loglevel error \-y \\  
  \-threads 2 \\  
  \-i "$IN" \\  
  \-vf "subtitles='${ASS}':force\_style='${FORCE\_STYLE}'" \\  
  \-c:v libx264 \-preset veryfast \-crf 18 \\  
  \-c:a copy \\  
  "$OUT"

\# Hand a tiny JSON back to n8n  
printf '{"output":"%s"}' "$OUT"

\-filter\_complex "\[0:v\]chromakey=0x00ff00:0.38:0.12\[ck\];\[ck\]despill=green\[out\]" \\
